workflow.name: SERP keyword ranking checker with RapidAPI & Google Sheets
workflow.description:
## üîç SERP Keyword Ranking Checker with RapidAPI & Google Sheets

**Automate keyword SERP ranking lookups** and log the data into Google Sheets using this no-code n8n workflow. Perfect for SEO professionals, digital marketers, or anyone tracking keyword visibility across regions.

---

## üß∞ Tools Used

- [**SERP Keyword Ranking Checker API**](https://rapidapi.com/PrineshPatel/api/serp-keyword-ranking-checker) ‚Äì Fetch real-time keyword SERP data
- **Google Sheets** ‚Äì Log keyword data for tracking, analysis, or client reporting

---

## üìå Workflow Overview

1. User submits a **keyword** and **country code** via an n8n form
2. Workflow sends a request to the **SERP Keyword Ranking Checker API**
3. API response is checked:
   - If **valid data is found**, it is logged to Google Sheets
   - If **no results are found**, a fallback message is saved instead
4. Optional delays added to space out operations

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Node-by-Node Breakdown

### 1. üü¢ Form Trigger: `On form submission`
- Accepts user input for:
  - `keyword` (e.g. "labubu")
  - `country` (e.g. "us")

### 2. üì¶ Set Node: `Global Storage`
- Stores form input into variables (`keyword`, `country`) for use in API requests and logging.

### 3. üåê HTTP Request: `SERP Keyword Ranking Checker`
- Sends a `POST` request to the [SERP Keyword Ranking Checker API](https://rapidapi.com/PrineshPatel/api/serp-keyword-ranking-checker) with:
  - `keyword`
  - `country`
- Includes headers:
  ```http
  x-rapidapi-host: serp-keyword-ranking-checker.p.rapidapi.com
  x-rapidapi-key: YOUR_RAPIDAPI_KEY
### 4. ‚öñÔ∏è If Node: Condition Checking

Checks whether the `serpResults` array returned by the API is non-empty.

- ‚úÖ **True Branch**: Proceeds if valid SERP data is available.
- ‚ùå **False Branch**: Proceeds if no SERP data is returned (e.g., empty result).

---

### 5. ‚è≥ Wait Node: 5-Second Delay

Adds a 5-second delay before proceeding to Google Sheets insertion.  
This helps control execution pace and ensures API rate limits or spreadsheet latency is handled smoothly.

- Used on **both True and False branches** for consistency.

---

### 6. üìä Google Sheets (Success Path)

Appends a new row into the selected Google Sheet with:

- `Keyword` ‚Äì the submitted keyword
- `Country` ‚Äì selected country code
- `Json data` ‚Äì full `serpResults` JSON array returned by the API

üí° Ideal for tracking keyword rankings over time or populating live dashboards.

---

### 7. üìä Google Sheets (Failure Path)

Appends a fallback message into the Google Sheet when no SERP results are found.

- `Keyword` ‚Äì the submitted keyword
- `Country` ‚Äì selected country code
- `Json data` ‚Äì `"No result found. Please try another keyword..."`

üîç Helps maintain a log of unsuccessful queries for debugging or auditing.

---
### üí° Use Cases

- **SEO Audits**  
  Automate keyword performance snapshots across different markets to identify opportunities and gaps.

- **Competitor Analysis**  
  Track keyword rankings of rival brands in real time to stay ahead of competition.

- **Client Reporting**  
  Feed live SERP data into dashboards or reports for transparent, real-time agency deliverables.

- **Content Strategy**  
  Discover which keywords surface top-ranking pages to guide content creation and optimization efforts.
---

### üîë How to Obtain Your API Key for SERP Keyword Ranking Checker API

1. **Sign Up or Log In**  
   Visit [RapidAPI](https://rapidapi.com/PrineshPatel/api/serp-keyword-ranking-checker) and create a free account using your email or social login.

2. **Go to the API Page**  
   Navigate to the [SERP Keyword Ranking Checker APi](https://rapidapi.com/PrineshPatel/api/serp-keyword-ranking-checker).

3. **Subscribe to the API**  
   Click **Subscribe to Test**, then choose a pricing plan that fits your needs (Free, Basic, Pro).

4. **Get Your API Key**  
   After subscribing, go to the **Security** tab on the API page to find your **X-RapidAPI-Key**.

5. **Use Your API Key**  
   Add the API key to your HTTP request headers:  
   ```http
   X-RapidAPI-Key: YOUR_API_KEY

parameters.content:
### 1. üü¢ **On form submission**
**Type:** `formTrigger`  
**Description:** Triggers when a user submits the form with `Keyword` & `Country` fields.

### 2. üì¶ **Global Storage**
**Type:** `set`  
**Description:** Stores the website value from the form for use in later nodes.

### 3. üåê **SERP Keyword Ranking Checker**
**Type:** `httpRequest`  
**Description:** Sends a POST request to the RapidAPI SERP Keyword Ranking Checker endpoint (`serp.php`) to get broad match keywords insights.

### 4. ‚öñÔ∏è **Condition Checking**
**Type:** `if`  
**Description:** Evaluates whether the response body contains non-empty data. If true, it proceeds down the "true" branch, otherwise it moves to the "false" branch for further actions. Ideal for handling conditional logic in workflows.

### 7. ‚è≥ **Wait Node (5-Second Interval)**
**Type:** `wait`  
**Description:** Introduces a 5-second delay in the workflow before moving to the next action. Ideal for controlling the flow of execution, pacing API calls, or ensuring sufficient time between operations.

### 5. ‚è≥ **Wait Node (5-Second Interval)**
**Type:** `wait`  
**Description:** Introduces a 5-second delay in the workflow before moving to the next action. Ideal for controlling the flow of execution, pacing API calls, or ensuring sufficient time between operations.

### 8. üìä **Google Sheets - Insert 'No result found' Record**
**Type:** `googleSheets`  
**Description:** This node inserts a record with the status "No result found" into a Google Sheet when no relevant data is found in the response body. Ideal for logging missing data, tracking errors, or maintaining a record of failed API requests.

**Key Features:**
- Automatically inserts "Not Found" when data is missing or unavailable.
- Customizable to log specific fields or add default messages.
- Can be used to maintain error tracking or data gaps in a structured sheet.

### 6. üìä **Google Sheets - Insert Record from Response Body**
**Type:** `googleSheets`  
**Description:** This node extracts data from the response body of a previous request and automatically inserts it into a specified Google Sheet. It allows for seamless data entry into your spreadsheet, making it ideal for logging, tracking, or storing information from API responses.

**Key Features:**
- Maps response body fields to sheet columns.
- Supports multiple rows of data insertion.
- Easily configurable with Google Sheets API credentials.

- [**SERP Keyword Ranking Checker API** (by PrineshPatel on RapidAPI)](https://rapidapi.com/PrineshPatel/api/serp-keyword-ranking-checker) ‚Äì Fetch real-time keyword SERP data
- **Google Sheets** ‚Äì Log keyword data for tracking, analysis, or client reporting

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
